<TITLE> PM, Mamata discuss rail cooperation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 bdnews24.com New Delhi Correspondent New Delhi, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)--India's railways minister Mamata Banerjee on Tuesday called on prime minister Sheikh Hasina, during her stay in the Indian capital, to discuss the details of cooperation between New Delhi and Dhaka for rail-projects in Bangladesh. "We are keen to step up bilateral cooperation in all fields, including the railway sector. I have had some discussions with prime minister Hasina and we will have more interactions both at the level of ministers and officials of the two countries in future," Banerjee told journalists after the meeting at the Hotel ITC Maurya. Dhaka will use a large chunk of the US $ 1 billion credit line that Indian prime minister Manmohan Singh announced for Bangladesh during his talks with Hasina on Monday for railway projects as well as for procuring locomotives and rail-coaches. Sources at the Indian railways ministry said that double-tracking the rail-link between Akhaura and Laksham, survey for improving rail connectivity to Khulna and Mongla and improvement of signaling system on Rajshahi-Parbatipur section could be among the projects for which Dhaka might ask Delhi to extend its assistance. In addition to the US $ 1 billion credit line, Singh on Monday told Hasina that India would also lay the rail-line between Akhaura and Agartala  the capital of the northeastern Indian state of Tripura. The Indian Railways expanded its network to Agartala last year. The issue of delay in customs clearance for Maitree Express between Kolkata and Dhaka also came up during discussion between Hasina and Banerjee, sources said. The meeting with railway minister was the last official engagement of Hasina in New Delhi on the second day of her t
